paragraphs.text: i found god on the corner of first and amistad. where the west was all but won. all alone smoking his last cigarette. i said: "where you been?" he said: "ask anything"
where were you when everything was falling apart? but all my days were spent by the telephone that never rang. and all i needed was a call that never came to the corner of first and amistad.
lost and insecure you found me you found me lying on the floor surrounded surrounded why'd you have to wait? where were you? where were you? just a little late you found me you found me
